&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic, enthusiastic individual to join Hub 1b of our Clinical Administration Service based at Breast Care Unit,Castle Hill Hospital on a 12 month fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be a key player in the administration team to manage the end to end clinical administrative processes associated to the patient pathways, ensuring a smooth and efficient service for both the multidisciplinary team and patients, in order to deliver a high quality administration service, for our patients and customers. Previous administration experience is essential, as is a willingness to learn and a willingness to help in all areas of the patient journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a team player with good communication and organisational skills, who is flexible in their approach to work. The post-holder will need to work independently in a diverse and interesting office environment, using their initiative to prioritise their workload, multi task and maintain confidentiality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will join a friendly and supportive team that values the contribution of all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is part time working days are Monday 1-5 Wednesday 8.30-4 (1 hours lunch)and Friday 8.30-5 (1 hours lunch)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;** Salary relates to year 3 of 3 year NHS pay deal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jennifer Beech - Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Jennifer.Beech@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
